## Core Truth

Lens answers one question — the question every CEO and CTO is asking:

> "Are we ready to migrate to an EU sovereign cloud?"

The answer is always one of four:

  ✅  Yes — migrate now.
      Score ≥ 90%, compliance clear, workarounds exist for remaining gaps.

  ⏳  Not yet — wait N months.
      Key blockers have announced EU equivalents arriving on a known timeline.
      We will alert you when the window opens.

  🔧  Not without changes — here's what needs to change.
      Critical services have no EU equivalent and no announced roadmap.
      Re-architecture is required before migration is viable.

  👀  Watching — you've set a threshold. We're monitoring the ecosystem.
      When your conditions are met, you'll be the first to know.

Everything Lens does — scanning, scoring, cataloguing, forecasting,
alerting — exists to produce one of these four answers, with the evidence
to back it up.

Lens is NOT a migration tool. It never touches production. It never
executes anything. It only reads, analyses, and watches.

AI explains. Noblinks Lens proves.

See: `specs/lens/ai clarification` for mandatory design constraints.

## Product Suite Context

Lens is the first product in a three-product suite:

  Lens   → `specs/lens/implementation plan`   (this file)
           "Are you ready to migrate?"
           Detects services, scores compatibility, flags compliance risks.

  Glance → `specs/glance/implementation plan`
           "What do I have and how does it all connect?"
           Full inventory + dependency graph + migration wave sequencing.
           Feeds into Guide as a structured blueprint export.

  Guide  → `specs/guide/implementation plan`
           "Here is your Hetzner blueprint. Let me walk you through building it."
           Blueprint generator + static migration guides + AI agent
           that guides the user step-by-step through creating infra on Hetzner,
           using the Hetzner API with an approval gate for every write action.

The output of Lens (compatibility score + compliance flags) feeds into Glance
and Guide. The output of Glance (dependency graph + migration waves) is the
primary input to Guide's blueprint generator.

