## PHASE 9 — Inventory, Scheduled Scans & Retention Loop

This phase transforms Lens from a one-time report tool into a continuously
valuable service. The discovery work is already done — this phase persists
and surfaces it.

### 9.0 — Retention Philosophy

**The core reframe:** Lens is not a report tool. It is a system users
track over time.

The product loop is:
```
Scan → Score → Improve → Drift → Repeat
```

Retention comes from ongoing clarity, not one-time reports. Every feature
in this phase serves one goal: give users a number they care about, show
them how to improve it, and notify them when it changes.

If only three things get built from this phase:
  1. EU Readiness KPI (score as a tracked metric with a target)
  2. Path to Improvement (quantified actions)
  3. Scheduled scans + Drift alerts

That is sufficient for strong retention.

