### 9.1 — Persistent Resource Inventory

**Why it retains:** Infrastructure changes constantly. A customer who
connects their AWS account once gets an always-current inventory of every
resource across all 91 service types — without ever having to think about
it. The inventory is only valuable if it stays fresh, which drives
re-scans.

**How it works:**
Each analysis already detects resources with IDs, names, types, regions,
and metadata. Currently this data is only used for the report and discarded.
This phase persists it as a first-class queryable inventory.

Schema addition:
```ts
lensInventory table:
  id, userId, accountId, sourceCloud
  service         // e.g. "ec2", "lambda", "rds"
  resourceId      // cloud-native ID
  resourceName    // human-readable name
  resourceType    // e.g. "t3.medium", "postgres14"
