### 9.3 — Drift Alerts

**What changed.** The core re-engagement loop.

Drift is any change that affects your sovereignty posture since the last
scan — whether caused by your team adding infrastructure or by EU clouds
improving their offerings. Lens detects both directions.

**Four drift types:**

🔴 **Sovereignty regression** (your score got worse)
  - New resource added that has no EU sovereign equivalent
  - "You added AWS Bedrock this week. No EU sovereign equivalent exists.
    Your OVHcloud score dropped 67% → 61%."
  - Triggered immediately after a scheduled scan detects the change

🟡 **New compliance exposure** (new flag triggered)
  - A new resource triggers a CLOUD Act, GDPR, or EU AI Act rule
  - "3 new Lambda functions detected. Serverless compute has no EU
    sovereign equivalent — CLOUD Act exposure increased."
  - "New Rekognition collection detected. High-risk category under
    EU AI Act Article 6. Compliance review required."

🟢 **Score improvement available** (EU cloud got better)
  - A catalog entry updated: match type improved from "none" → "partial"
    or "partial" → "compatible" for a service in the customer's inventory
  - "Scaleway launched managed Kubernetes. You have 3 EKS clusters.
    Your Scaleway score can improve from 52% → 67%. Re-scan to confirm →"
  - Targeted: only sent to customers who actually have that service

🔵 **Inventory change** (neutral — informational)
  - Resources added or removed since last scan
  - "14 new resources detected, 3 decommissioned since last scan.
    See what changed →"

**Delivery:**
- Email (primary) — clean digest format, one email per drift event or
  daily/weekly digest depending on preference
- In-app notification badge on Lens sidebar
- Each alert links directly to the relevant section of the report

**Why this is differentiated:**
No other tool does sovereignty drift detection. Terraform has config drift.
Datadog has metric drift. Nobody watches whether your infrastructure is
drifting away from EU sovereignty compliance. That's the gap.

