### 9.9 — Migration Readiness Forecast ("When should we move?")

**The killer feature. This is where Lens becomes a strategic platform.**

The problem it solves: Management sees 75% readiness, says "not good
enough, let's wait" — and does nothing. There is no signal to act on.
No way to know if waiting is the right call or how long to wait.

Lens solves this by tracking the EU cloud ecosystem itself — not just
your infrastructure — and forecasting when your readiness will improve
without you changing anything.

**What it shows:**

```
Current score:          75%  (today)
Projected (3 months):   83%  (medium confidence)
Projected (6 months):   91%  (low-medium confidence)

Why:
  → Scaleway Serverless Functions: expanding runtime support · ETA Q3 2026
  → OVHcloud Managed Kubernetes: GA expected Q2 2026
  → Hetzner Load Balancer v2: HTTP/3 + gRPC support · Q3 2026

Blockers with no announced roadmap:
  → AWS PrivateLink equivalent: not announced on any EU cloud
  → Cognito-compatible managed identity: partial only (Keycloak)
```

**The "Wait vs Move" recommendation (deterministic, not AI):**

```
Recommendation: Wait — re-evaluate in 6 months

Reason:
  2 of your 4 critical blockers have announced equivalents
  arriving Q2–Q3 2026. Migrating now requires significant
  re-architecture. In 6 months the same migration carries
  low risk.

We will notify you when:
  → Your OVHcloud readiness crosses 90%
  → Scaleway Serverless Functions reaches GA
  → Any critical blocker gets an announced roadmap entry
```

**Why this is GOLD for retention:**

Users who set a migration threshold and wait for Lens's signal never
cancel. They are subscribed to the ecosystem, not to a report. Lens
becomes the system that tells them *when* to move. That is a permanent
seat at the table.

New retention loop:
```
Scan → Score → Forecast → Set Threshold → Wait → Alert → Decide → Act
```

