#### 9.9.1 — EU Cloud Roadmap Dataset (core data layer)

This is maintained like the catalog — human-curated, NOT AI-generated.
AI summarizes. Humans research and verify.

Sources to monitor:
  - EU cloud changelogs and release notes
  - Public product roadmaps (OVHcloud, Scaleway, Hetzner blog)
  - Conference talks and product announcements
  - GitHub repos (open-source components of EU clouds)
  - Documentation additions (new service pages appearing)

Schema:
```ts
interface RoadmapEntry {
  targetCloud: TargetCloud
  capability: string         // e.g. "compute.function", "database.cassandra"
  currentMatch: "none" | "partial"
  projectedMatch: "partial" | "compatible"
  status: "announced" | "in_beta" | "ga_imminent" | "rumoured" | "not_announced"
  eta: string | null         // e.g. "Q3 2026", "H1 2026", null if unknown
  confidence: "high" | "medium" | "low"
  source: string             // URL to announcement / release note
  notes: string              // what specifically is changing
  lastVerified: string       // ISO date — when a human last confirmed this
}
```

Critical rule: `eta` and `confidence` must be sourced from a real
announcement. Never infer or estimate without a source. If unknown,
`eta: null`. Integrity of this dataset is the product's credibility.

